Rating: 1
I tried this dish because it was the first I had seen on this site that rated 4 forks from everyone. I'm sorry to be the party pooper but it just did not impress us. The lamb was marinated 24 hours as instructed and the marinade flavor completely overwhelmed the lamb. Not overly crazy about the sauce either. Try this - an early 90's recipe from Martha Stewart: Trim a rack VERY well, rub room temp lamb with a paste made of crushed garlic, cracked black pepper, olive oil. Sear in a hot skillet being careful not to crack the crust. Finish in a 500 degree oven for about 5 minutes for medium rare. We have made this repeatedly over the past ten years and IT ALWAYS gets rave reviews even with ordinary supermarket lamb. New Years Eve 2000, when I made it with lamb from the market with the ungodly prices, it was out of this world.

