Rating: 4
I used dried cilantro & shaoshing wine in the marinade, halving the marinade and the sauce and using it on 2 shoulder chops, which I then sauteed quickly in olive oil. I made the sauce as specified, except I mixed in the remains of the marinade and added a little chilli sauce, lemon juice, and brown sugar to taste. I only used 1/8 of the butter called for, and it was still great. A really tasty and different lamb chop dish. Addendum: I've since used just the marinade on a boneless New York steak, broiled till rare, and it was amazing--excellent flavor, and the sauce became completely unnecessary. I will make this again and again.

